# rag Directory Guide

The [rag/](mdc:rag) directory contains the core logic for retrieval-augmented generation, including:

- [prompts.py](mdc:rag/prompts.py): Prompt templates and logic for RAG workflows.
- [settings.py](mdc:rag/settings.py): Configuration settings for RAG modules.
- [raptor.py](mdc:rag/raptor.py): Raptor-specific logic and utilities.
- [benchmark.py](mdc:rag/benchmark.py): Benchmarking tools for RAG performance.
- [utils/](mdc:rag/utils): Utility functions and helpers.
- [nlp/](mdc:rag/nlp): Natural language processing components.
- [llm/](mdc:rag/llm): Large language model integration.
- [app/](mdc:rag/app): Application logic and endpoints.
- [res/](mdc:rag/res): Resource files for RAG modules.
- [svr/](mdc:rag/svr): Server-side logic for RAG.

See each referenced file or subdirectory for more details on its role in the RAG pipeline.
